title: Hesaketvmeset Likes
Aeha! Kut! Cv Hesayecv
Rvne Kalfvle Hocefken
Pu Hesayecvn Pu Hesayecvn
lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Pu Hesayecvn,
Pu Hesayecvn,
Pu Hesayecvn hecvks!
Aeha! Kalfvle mimvn,
Eto-teweklepkv mvn,
Oh vtarket estemerkvtes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Mvn oh vtarkof,
Mvn oh vtarkof,
E catvt pvlatkvtes,
Hvse tis yomociken,
Cvtot tefvlahlvtes,
Pu Hesayecv elofvhkvn.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Hopelakvtes,
Hopelakvtes,
Este vcacakatet,
Momen nettv tutcenof,
Hvtvm akvwapiket,
Em estvlken etehecvtes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
Mv nettvn hecof,
Mv nettvn hecof,
Herkvn vwahlepvtes,
Momet herkvn vwahlof,
Hvlwe min ayepvtes,
Mvn er like munkv rvnet.
Pu Hesayecvn Pu Hesayecvn Continued
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
Pum fvtcecatet,
Pum fvtcecatet,
Erken kice munkvt os,
Aeha! Cvrke toyetskat,
Vnet em eliyvtes,
Cent em meriyet, hesahuecvs.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 6}
Em merrvkares!
Em merrvkares!
Naorketvn wikaket,
V coh awen omate,
Vn cvnaken hahihcit,
Em meriyit, hesahuecares.
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Our Savior,
Our Savior,
See our Savior!
Alas! There at Calvary,
The cross where,
He hung and suffered.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
There He hung,
There He hung,
He shed His blood,
The sun became dark,
The rock split,
When our Savior died.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
They buried Him,
They buried Him,
The people that was dear to Him,
Then on the third day,
He rose again,
He saw His people. (deciples)
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
When He saw that day,
When He saw that day,
He gave them peace,
When He gave them peace,
He went up to heaven,
There He’ll stay forever.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
He made our decision,
He made our decision,
He still says to the Father,
Alas! You are my Father,
I died for you,
Have compassion and save them.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 6}
I will have pity on them!
I will have pity on them!
They will sin no more,
If they will come to me,
I will make them mine,
I will have compassion and save them.
{end_of_verse}

title: Vn Herketvn Cem Wikvkis
lyrics:
Ekvnv es temat onkon,
Ce feken penkvlehcatskvs”,
Cesvs kicet ’monayvtes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Ayiyvtet rvlakiyof,
Cvnaken ce hayvkares,
Momen estvn likiyate,
Cemeu mvn vpokatskvres.
Afvcketvt cem ocvkes,
Holwayeckv vkerrickv,
Orvte seko tvlofvn”.
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
Not as the world gives you,
Let not your heart be afraid”,
Jesus said as He spoke to them.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
I will go but when I return,
I will make you mine,
Then where I am,
You will be there also.
You will have happiness,
Thoughts of sin,
Will not reach heaven”.
{end_of_verse}

title: Puyvfekcv Herat Vhtet
Cehofv Cv’rke Toyetskat
lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Cehofv Cv’rke toyetskat!
Hvlwe mahen liketskvt,
Nak omvlkvn hayetskvtes,
Omvlkvn ohfvnketskvt,
Cv hompicvs! Cv hompicvs!
Momen hvtvm ci ’yacus.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Cesvs, vn hesse toyetskat!
Vnen vm eletskvtes,
Naorkv toyis, vm merrvs,
Vm puyvfekcvn ce’mis,
Cv hompicvs! Cv hompicvs!
Momen hvtvm ci ’yacus.
Pumen pu kicetskvtes,
Ehlekos,” maketskvtes,
Cv hompicvs! Cv hompicvs!
Momen hvtvm ci ’yacus.
Pumen pu kicetskvtes,
Ehlekos”, maketskvtes,
Mvn cvskuecvs! Mvn cvskuecvs!
Momen vcafvckares.
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Jehovah, You are my Father!
You live way above,
You made everything,
You are over everything,
Feed me! Feed me!
Then again, I want more.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Jesus, You are my friend!
You died for me,
I am a sinner, have mercy on me,
I give you my spirit,
Feed me! Feed me!
Then again, I want more.
You said to us,
Will never die”. You said,
Feed me! Feed me!
Then again, I want more.
You said to us,
Will never die,” You said,
Give me that to drink! Give me that to drink!
Then I will be happy.
{end_of_verse}

title: Elkv-este Toyis
Este-hopelkv Ahuehkan
Hesaketvmese Vm Merrvs
lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Hesaketvmese! Vm merrvs! Vm merrvs!
Hesaketvmese! Vm merrvs!
Hesaketvmese! Vm merret cv ’sepvs!
Cenaken cv hayvs! Cv hayvs! Cv hayvs!
Cenaken cv hayvs! Cv hayvs!
Cv sumkepvnt omis, vm merretsks!
Vm merretsks!
Cv sumkepvnt omis, vm merretsks!
Cv sumkepvnt omis, vm merretske munken!
Cem e wikit omis, vm merrvs! Vm merrvs!
Ceme e wikit omis, vm merrvs!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Send one who makes me happy! Send!
Send one who makes me happy!
When you send the one who makes me happy!
I’ll go where there is no death! I’ll go!
I’ll go where there is no death!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
Let peace come, while I sing! While I sing!
Let peace come, while I sing!
Let peace come, make me happy!
Heavenly peace is where I will go! I will go!
Heavenly peace is where I will go!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
Good (Holy) Spirit! Send us! Send us!
Good (Holy) Spirit! Send us!
Good (Holy) Spirit! Be with me!
Your heavenly place, I will live! I will live!
Your heavenly place! I will live!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 6}
No death in heaven! Heaven!
No death in heaven!
No death in heaven, peace forever!
I will live there forever! I will live there!
I will live there forever!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 7}
I sing songs about peace! I sing!
I sing songs about peace!
I continue to sing songs of peace!
I will live in everlasting peace. I will live,
I will live in everlasting peace!
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
2
God! Forgive me! Forgive me!
God! Forgive me!
God! Forgive me and take me!
Make me yours! Make me! Make me!
Make me yours! Make me!
When I’m lost, forgive me!
Forgive me!
When I’m lost, forgive me!
When I’m lost, continue to forgive me!
I give myself to you, forgive me! Forgive me!
I give myself to you, forgive me!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Vc afvcecicvn atotvs! Atotvs!
Vc afvcecicvn atotvs!
Vc afvcecicvn a vcoh totetsken!
Elkv sekate min vyares! Vyares!
Elkv sekate min vyares!
Hesaketvmese Vm Merrvs Continued
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
Herkvt vlvkekvs, yvhikin! Yvhikin!
Herkvt vlvkekvs, yvhikin!
Herkvt alvkekvs, vc afvcecicvs!
Herkv tvlofv min vyares! Vyares!
Herkv tvlofv min ayvres!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
Puyvfekcv Heran! Atotvs! Atotvs!
Puyvfekcv Heran! Atotvs!
Puyvfekcv Heran! Vc vpayecetsken!
Cen liketv heran, likares! Likares!
Cen liketv heran! Likares!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 6}
Elkv sekate mi tvlofvn! Tvlofvn!
Elkv sekate mi tvlofvn!
Elkv sekate mi, herkv emunkaten!
Estofis emunkvn likares! Likares!
Estofis emunkvn likares!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 7}
Herkv yvhiketvn yvhikit! Yvhikit!
Herkv yvhiketvn yvhikit!
Herkvn yvhiketvn yvhikiye munket!
Herkv yuksv-sekan likares. Likares,
Herkv yuksv-sekan likares!
{end_of_verse}

title: Cesvs Tawvt Pun Hesset Os
title_en: “What a Friend We Have In Jesus”
lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}

Cesvs tawvt pun hesset os,
Nak pun honnat kvwapes,
Mekusapkvt nak omvlkvn,
’Soh vpeyeye tayes,
Afvcketvt pun sumiken,
Tewolen pu ’stemerkes,
Mekusapkvt nak omvlkvn,
Cesvs ’soh vpeyekok.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Punrvpkv ocvket o haks?
Pu feknokhoket o haks?
Pum enhonrkvn wihkeyates?
Cesvs ’soh vpeyvkes,
Pum hesse etv mv omat,
Esheceye taye haks?
Pun yekce-sekaten kerras,
Monkv ’soh vpeyvkes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Vkerrickvt ’poh wetenke,
Pum honhoyat fulle haks?
Cesvs pum vnicvt omes,
Monkv ’soh vpeyvkes,
Cen hessvlket cem wikakof,
Cesvs em onvyvkes,
E sakpv ’sece ’cayecen,
Herkvt ece ’pakares.
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}

Only Jesus is our friend,
He bears our heavy burdens,
All things in prayer,
We should always take to him,
Our joy will leave,
Our sorrow will be near,
All things in prayer,
If we do not take it to Jesus.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Have we adversaries?
Have we sorrows?
When we lose hope?
Let us go to Jesus,
Our friend, like no other,
We can find none better?
He knows our weakness,
Let us go. (to Him).
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Our thoughts oppressed,
Do we go about in sorrors?
Jesus is our helper,
Let us go, (to Him),
When your friends leave you,
Tell it to Jesus,
I want to be in his arms,
You will have peace.
{end_of_verse}

title: Cesvs ’Mapohicvt
lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Cesvs ’mapohicvt,
Em afvckakuses,
’Mvkerrickv Hvlwen em oces,
Em afvcketvhkvn,
Hvtuse en heckat,
Tulaswv onayeko tayes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Heyv afvcketv,
Cvnaken hayiyvnks,
Cesvs ofvn esheciyofv,
Mont vkvsamiyof,
Cesvs en hocefkv,
Ofvn vc afackuse hakvnks.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Cesvs kerriyofv,
Vc afackusvnkes,
Em estvlkeu afackakuset,
Estonko tetayet,
Homvn tvkpvlatket,
Cesvs e mekusapvkvnkes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
Cesvs em afackit,
Yvhikin yafkvnkes,
Cesvs ’Mapohicvt Continued
Alas! All people should know!
He loved me,
He suffered for me,
He bought me.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
’Mvnokeckv tvrpvn,
Es cv kvwapiken,
Naorketv mv ofvn wikit,
Mont cv ’stemeriket,
Cv feke nokikes,
Komet akvsvmkv ocvkvnks.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 6}
Vm etektvniken,
Vn hiyayakusen,
Elicv ayvte omiyvnks,
Vm puyvfekcvhkvn,
Mvn akvwapkvnkes,
Hvresse cvlecvn likvnkes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 7}
Aeha! Mv nak here,
Acake ocate,
Cesvs a osset on kerriyvnks,
Cesvs vc vpakof,
Vc afacecicvnks,
En herkvt cv fvcket on omvnks.
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Those who listen to Jesus,
How happy are they,
Their thoughts are always toward heaven,
Their happiness was,
From the beginning,
The tongue cannot describe.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
This happiness,
I made mine,
When I found it in Jesus,
And I believed,
In the name of Jesus,
I became happy.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
When I came to know Jesus,
I became happy,
His people are happy,
When they could do nothing else,
They fell down before Him,
And prayed to Jesus.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
I am happy with Jesus,
I sing until evening,
Aeha! Este omvl’ kerrates!
Vc vnokecvtes,
Vm estemerrvtes,
Vnen cv nesatet omvtes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
His wings of love,
Lifted me up,
In that, I quit sinning,
Again I was suffering,
My heart was hurting,
I was without faith.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 6}
I was giving time,
It was revealed to me,
I went as Elijah,
My spirit,
At that momet, arose,
The moon was sitting under me.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 7}
Alas! That good thing,
That is precious,
I knew it came from Jesus,
When Jesus is with me,
It makes me happy,
His peace filled within me.
{end_of_verse}

title: Cesvs Cv Hoyanet V’tskvs
lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Cesvs cv hoyanet v’tskvs,
Huehkvyat pohvs,
Vpvltaken em merretskof,
Vn cvwihketskvs.
Chorus:
Jesus Jesus hear my call,
While on others you are calling,
Do not leave me.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Cem ohliketv ehomvn,
Cem vtokkekit,
Merkvn cem pohepvyofvn,
Lvpken vm merrvs.
Sing chorus:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Cen herkv tvlken enhonrit,
Ye cen tvk latkis,
Puyvfekcv vnvttaten,
Vme wicecvs.
Sing chorus:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
Mahlvpvtketv omvlkvn,
V’metske tayes,
Vc vpaketskekon omat,
V’ntvlket omes.
Sing chorus:
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Jesus do not pass me by,
Hear my call,
While on others you give mercy,
Do not leave me.
Cesvs Cesvs huehkvyat pohvs,
Vpvltaken enhuehketskof,
Vn cv wihketskvs.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Before your throne,
I kneel,
I ask for your mercy,
Forgive me quickly.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Trusting only in your grace,
I fall down before you,
With a wounded spirit,
Heal me.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
All thy comfort,
You could give me,
If you are not with me,
I am alone.
{end_of_verse}

title: Tecakkeyvte Emekusapvlke
Vm Munkuset
title_en: “Just as I am, without one plea.”
lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}
2
Come to me, you say to me,
Your blood was shed for me,
That’s all that I can say,
Savior, I come, I come!
I come to you, my spirit,
With all his sins,
Your blood cleanses it,
Savior, I come, I come!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Cv ’stemerrus’, cv hecekot,
Vn ’yvfekcv en heleswv,
Ceme ofvn eshecaret,
Hesayeca, Atis, Atis!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
Cv nvfhokis, hueriye ’munk’s,
Penkvlkv sulket cv nafken,
Cv feke nokkuse emunk’s,
Hesayeca, Atis, Atis!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
Vm munkusen, cv’setskvres,
Holwvyeckvn vn kvpicvs,
Cem punvkvn ’kvsamikv,
Hesayeca, Atis, Atis!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 6}
Cem vnokeckv kerkekat,
Enrvpkv omvl’ lekafes,
Monk’ cenak’ toyiyat tvlkus,
Hesayeca, Atis, Atis!
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Vc oh vtes, cv kicetskes,
Ce catv vm pvlatkvten,
Mv tvlken punayecit os,
Hesayeca, Atis, Atis!
Ec oh atis, vn ’yvfekcv,
En holwayeckv omvlkvn,
Ce catv hvsvtecet os,
Hesayeca, Atis, Atis!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
In my sufferings, I am blind,
My spirits healing,
I will find in you,
Savior, I come, I come!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
Though I’m struck, I still stand,
I am stricken with much fear,
My heart still aches,
Savior, I come, I come!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
You will take me just as I am,
Separate me from sin,
I’m a believer of your word,
Savior, I come, I come!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 6}
Thy love unknown,
All barriers are broken down,
I am yours alone,
Savior, I come, I come!
{end_of_verse}

title: Vm Vnicvs
Vwakes, Vwakes, Vwakes
Cesvs Vcvnokeces
lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Cesvs vcvnokeces,
Cokv-rakkot cvkices,
Hopuetaket enaket’s,
Yekcvkekis, ent yekces.
Chorus:
(Yes Jesus) loves me,
(Yes Jesus) loves me,
(Yes Jesus) loves me,
The book (Bible) tells me (so).
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Cesvs vm elvtet os,
Encuko vnhaukvren,
Holwvyeckvn vslecen,
’Mestucet eceyvres.
Sing chorus:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Cvyekceko estomis,
Vcvnokece monkvts,
Hvlwen a vfvnnaket,
Vc vhecice monkvts.
Sing chorus:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
Ekvnvn ropottvyof,
Vcvpake monkvres,
Vnokecin omate,
Ca’lofvn cv’sepvres.
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Jesus loves me (this I know),
The Bible tells me (so),
Little ones to Him belong,
They are weak but He is strong.
Vcvnokeces,
Vcvnokeces,
Vcvnokeces,
Nakcokvt cvkices.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Jesus died for me,
His house is open to me,
Sins He has erased,
(Let) His little child go in.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Tho I am weak,
He still loves me,
Watching from on high,
He watches over me.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
When I pass thru this world,
He is with me,
If I love Him,
When I die He will take me.
{end_of_verse}

title: Cesvs Purket Hvlwen Likes
Prayer Hymn, Funeral Hymn
Ce Mekusapeyvte
Pu Hayvte Toyetskate!
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
title_en: “Christ has Gone To Prepare a Place for Us”
lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
Ra’ pum etetakuecet,
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
Pu Hesayecvt!
En yekcetv pum vnicvn,
Pum wihket, kvwapkvtes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
Ra’ pum etetakuecet,
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
Pu Hesayecvt!
En herketv pum vnicvn,
Pum wihket, kvwapkvtes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
Ra’ pum etetakuecet,
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
Pu Hesayecvt!
En ’yvfekcv pum vnicvn,
Pum wihket, kvwapkvtes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
Ra’ pum etetakuecet,
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
Pu Hesaycecvt!
Mekusapkv ’sem vhakvn,
Pum wihket kvwapkvtes.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
Ra’ pum etetakuecet,
Ayvtes! Ayvtes!
Pu Hesayecvt!
Aksumketv ’sem vhakvn,
Pum wihket kvwapkvtes.
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
He’s gone! He’s gone!
To prepare a place for us,
He’s gone! He’s gone!
Our Savior!
He helps us with His strength,
He left it for us, and arose.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
He’s gone! He’s gone!
To prepare a place for us,
He’s gone! He’s gone!
Our Savior!
He helps us with His peace,
He left it for us, and arose.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
He’s gone! He’s gone!
To prepare a place for us,
He’s gone! He’s gone!
Our Savior!
He helps us with His Spirit,
He left it for us, and arose.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
He’s gone! He’s gone!
To prepare a place for us,
He’s gone! He’s gone!
Our Savior!
He taught us prayer,
He left it for us and arose.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
He’s gone! He’s gone!
To prepare a place for us,
He’s gone! He’s gone!
Our Savior!
He taught us to baptise,
He left it for us, and arose.
{end_of_verse}

title: Vpeyet Vkvsamvks
Cvto Enhvteceskv
lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Cvto enhvteceskv,
Em eyuksv tis seko,
Vm ehketv toyetskat,
Ec ofvn ehkvranis,
Holwvyeckv rakrakvt,
Vnen vn kvpakekvs.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Eto svrahketskofv,
Uewv catv esyome,
Ce nvce vfihnvtet,
Mvt cv hvsvtecekvs,
Momet cen cvpvkketvn,
Hopiyen vkueyekvs.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Cv turopuswvt ocet,
Pvlatke munken omis,
Momen heren fekcakhit,
Wikvko munken omis,
Mvt holwvyeckv hvmkis,
Vm vkueyeko tayes.
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
The beginning the rock,
That will never end,
You are my hiding place,
I will hide in you,
With sins so big,

{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Nailed to the tree,
Water and blood together,
Flowed from your side,
You cleansed me,
Then your wrath,
Moved far away.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
My tears that I have,

And I am very jealous,
Yet I can not quit,
That one sin,
I can not move from me.
{end_of_verse}

lyrics_en:

We can see it afar.
Oketv cvmpusan,
Mi tvpalv mimvn herusan,

Mi tvpalv teheceyvres.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}

We shall sorrow no more,
We will have eternal rest.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Our Father is there with full forgiveness,

He loved us so much,
He still has forgiveness.
Ekvnv Herusat Ocet Os Continued
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
We will have joy on that beautiful shore,
We will be with the saved,
Our labor will be over,
We will be with the creator.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
We shall meet, and sing together,
Where the saved never die,
And there will be no more sin,
There will be neither sorrow nor pain.
{end_of_verse}

.

{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}

Mvt ce yekcice tares,
Cen rvpvlke sulke mahis,

{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}

Mvt epu ’fvcecices,
Vkvsvmkv esyvhik’tvn,
Pu ’fvcket yvhikeyof.
Sing chorus:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}

Sing chorus;
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Take the name of Jesus,
Person of sorrow,
He will give you joy,
Take it where’er you go.
Hocefkv vcakat,
Ekvnv ’menhonrkv tes,
Hocefkv cvmpusat,
Hvlwen afvcecices.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Take the name of Jesus,
He will make you strong,
Tho you have many adversaries,
Call on the Lord quickly.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Jesus precious name!
That will keep us happy,
Singing the songs of faith,
As we sing happily.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
When they hear the name of Jesus,
They will kneel before Him,
Saying praises to Him.
{end_of_verse}

lyrics:
{start_of_verse: 1}

Hvyvyvket fihnet os.
Chorus:
Yes, we will see each other there,
The beautiful, the beautiful river,
Gathering with the saints,
We will gather together.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Uerakko vfopke mimvn,
Pu ’fvcket yvkvpeyvres,
Pu Hesayecvn ’kvsamet,
Epu ’facke munkvres.
Sing chorus:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}

Nak pun honnat apvlaten,
Merkvt cvto-kunaplane,
Kvpvtokvn pu’mvres.
Sing chorus:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
Uewv est’ afvcecicat!
Mv mekusapvlke elkvt,
Estofis etekvpicekat,
’Kvsvmkvn kvwapkvres.
Sing chorus:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
Ue’ tokunap-hvtke oman,
Lvpken eroriceyvres,
Herkv esyvhiket vhkvn,
Epu ’fvcecicvres.
Sing chorus:
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{start_of_verse: 1}
Shall we gather at the river?
Where Jesus’ angels trod?
Flowing from Jesus,
The light is flowing.
Momis, mvn teheceyvres,
Uerakko herusen, esherusen,
Mekusapvken etohkvliket,
Fulleye monkv tares.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
There beside the river,
We will be happy as we walk,
We will believe on our Savior,
We will be happy forever.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Before we get to the river,
We cast away our heavy burdens,
Mercy is golden,
We will receive a crown.
Uerakkon Heruse Continued
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
The water makes people happy!
The Christians death,
Never separate,
Believing they will rise.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 5}
The water is like silver,
Soon we shall arrive,
Singing a song of peace,
It will make us happy.
{end_of_verse}

title: Merretv omvl’ Pucaset
lyrics:
To the tune
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 1}
Merretv omvl’ Pucaset,
Cv feken yvhikuecvs,
Cen yvmvskv fihne munkvn,
’Svn hueketsken yvhikis,
Yvhiketv hvlwe ocan,
Mvn es v mvhayeckat!
Afvcketv hvlwe ocan,
Cen herkvn ’sv kvwapkis.
Merretv Omvl’ continued
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
Mekusapkvn ce kvwapis,
Mimvn oretvn komit,
Monkv cv komecken omat,
Ce huten er orares,
Cehofv en sumkiyofvn,
Cesvs es cv hecvtes,
E catvn es cv nesvtes,
Naorketvn wikaren.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
Nettv omvl’ ce naorkit,
Ce tenrapiye ’munkvts,
Cv feke fekhonnekaten,
Cen herkvn ’svm en huehkvs!
Cv sumke tetayet omes,
Vm vnicecketkate,
Monkv cen herkv vcakan,
Cv feken ’svm oh coyvs.
{end_of_verse}
lyrics_en:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 1}
Master of all blessing,
Make my heart sing,
Your meekness still flowing,
I sing songs of our calling,
Songs from heaven,
Teach me from there!
Happiness from heaven,
Your grace will raise me.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
I raise prayers up to you,
Trying to reach there,
But, if you desire,
I will come to your home,
When I get lost from Jehovah,
Jesus will find me,
He bought me with his blood,
I will sin no more.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
I sin everyday,
Against you,
Stop my (wandering) heart,
Your grace calls for me!
Even I could of been lost,
(If) you didn’t help me,
So your precious grace,
Write it on my heart.
{end_of_verse}
